venues.name: H-E-B Center at Cedar Park

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: Regular Hours - Monday - Friday 10:00 am - 6:00 pm, weekend hours vary per event. For event box office hours, please visit www.HEBcenter.com All H-E-B Center at Cedar Park event tickets can be purchased through Ticketmaster.
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Cash, American Express, VISA, Mastercard, Discover
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Monday - Friday from 10:00 am - 6:00 pm at the Box Office located near the East Entrance. Event will call tickets may be picked up two hours prior to the event. Policies for each event may vary.

venues.parkingDetail: All parking at H-E-B Center at Cedar Park is cash only. Parking is available in Lots A, B, F, G, H, I. Prices range from $10 to $20 based on event. VIP Parking is available on the east side of the building via the 2nd 183A South entrance. Cash only for all self-park and valet lots
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Tickets for H-E-B Center at Cedar Park events can be purchased by visiting the Box Office, or by calling 1-800-745-3000. Tickets can also be purchased through www.Ticketmaster.com. Please indicate the need for visually impaired or hearing-impaired seating to the ticket seller. If an interpreter is needed, please contact our marketing department at 512-600-5000 a minimum of three weeks prior to the event so appropriate accommodations can be made. H-E-B Center at Cedar Park provides accessible seating on each level and within each price range for any given event subject to availability Wheelchair companion seats are reserved for the companions of guests in wheelchairs. The number of companion seats available depends upon the number of wheelchair users and companion seats sold and the number of conventional seats sold closest to the desired accessible seating area in each of the ticket categories.

generalInfo.childRule: Ticket Requirements: For all ticketed events, all H-E-B Center at Cedar Park patrons must present a ticket for entry, except for those patrons younger than two (2) years of age. However, children under two years of age must sit on the lap of an accompanying ticket-bearing adult. For some family/kids events ages one (1) and up must be accompanied by a ticket.

boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: Please call (512) 301-6600 for ticket and parking information.
boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: The Grand Plaza Box Office is only open during event hours. For a full list of Circuit of The Americas events, visit thecircuit.com/events. The Box Office typically opens 1 hour prior to gates opening. Times are subject to change. Call (512) 301-6600 for more information.
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: American Express, Visa, MasterCard, Discover, Cash
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Photo ID and credit card used to make purchase are required.

venues.parkingDetail: Standard parking (typically in Lot A, E, F or H) is included with the purchase of an ABFC ticket. Parking locations are always subject to change. Premium parking (Lot B, C and D) is available for purchase per game while supply lasts to park closer to the main entrance of the venue.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: ADA seating is available in both the North Stand and the South Stand. In the South Stand, ADA seats are at the bottom of the section, in sections 120-123. In the North Stand, ADA seats are at the top of the section, in sections 102-103.

generalInfo.generalRule: Visit thecircuit.com/faq for a list of venue policies.
generalInfo.childRule: Children ages 2 and under are FREE with a ticketed adult, assuming they do not require their own reserved seat. If the child requires their own seat, a full price ticket must be purchased
